modules.description: Measures time intervals using nanosecond-resolution timestamps and retrieves clock period information when available. It operates with integer64 values to represent time durations and clock periods. Used to calculate precise timing differences in performance-critical applications or hardware synchronization tasks.

Provides functions to define and execute unit tests, including a check function for asserting conditions and a run function for executing test callbacks. Works with test callbacks and testable values that support equality checks. Used to validate code correctness with colored output and selective test execution.

provides timing and testing capabilities for asynchronous code, combining precise time measurement with test execution. It uses 64-bit integers for time durations and clock periods, enabling accurate performance analysis and synchronization. Tests are run as Lwt promises, with results printed directly to the console. It supports measuring execution intervals and handling asynchronous exceptions in a MirageOS environment.
